quote_last: the fog dissolves completely and the black boys are telling Acutes to clear the floor for the meeting. All the tables are carried out of the day room to the tub room across the hall—leaves the floor, McMurphy says, like we was aiming to have us a little dance.
title: One Flew Over the Cuckoo’s Nest
author: Ken Kesey
